docs.abstract: The man charged in a shooting at a Walmart that left 22 people dead had railed in a manifesto about “the Hispanic invasion of Texas.”

docs.lead_paragraph: EL PASO — A federal grand jury on Thursday indicted the suspect in last summer’s mass shooting at an El Paso Walmart on federal hate crime charges, accusing the 21-year-old former college student of targeting Hispanics in a racially motivated massacre that left 22 people dead.

headline.main: Federal Hate Crime Charges Filed in El Paso Shooting That Targeted Latinos
